.TH "netdev_get_name" 9 "netdev_get_name" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
netdev_get_name \- get a netdevice name, knowing its ifindex.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" netdev_get_name
.BI "(struct net *net "  ","
.BI "char *name "  ","
.BI "int ifindex "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "net" 12
network namespace
.IP "name" 12
a pointer to the buffer where the name will be stored.
.IP "ifindex" 12
the ifindex of the interface to get the name from.
